 Dradis Framework 2.6.1 - Release Notes
=======================================
 -- version 2.6.1, Feb 11th, 2011 --
  -- http://dradisframework.org --

What is new
-----------
Several minor fixes have been introduced in this release:

* Update Rails to 3.0.4 and RedCloth to 4.2.6
* Update the SSL certificate for 2011 (see ./server/conf/ssl/README)
* Try to better deal with the way Burp Scanner output files use null bytes
* Improve verify.sh to find Bundler even when not in the PATH
* Fix the start.sh script to use UNIX forward slash instead of Windows


Bugs Fixed
----------

Known Issues
------------


Installing
----------
As always the release ships with a windows installer,
dradis-v2.6.1-setup.exe, and the platform independent packages,
dradis-v2.6.1.tar.bz2 and dradis-v2.6.1.tar.gz. This can all be
downloaded from the website [i]. 

For Linux prerequisite instructions please see readme.txt or [ii].


